hopobject.body: I'm training to be an engineer advantmed.com Airline ticketing classes, and their associated restrictions, are fiendishly complicated and vary from airline to airline. The rule of thumb is that if you buy one of the airline’s cheapest advance fares you will probably have to be very flexible with making date changes later on. It is not simply a matter of paying more to upgrade to a higher class of economy seat, as the airline will hold some seats back to get top dollar from late bookers.
